parameters.content:
## üéØ GOOGLE FORMS TRIGGER

**Choose**:
‚Ä¢ **Webhook**: Instant (Forms ‚Üí Sheets ‚Üí Webhook URL)
‚Ä¢ **Sheets Trigger**: Polls responses sheet

**Google Forms Setup**:
1. Responses ‚Üí New spreadsheet
2. Tools ‚Üí Script editor ‚Üí Webhook code
3. Copy Webhook URL from n8n

**Fields expected**: rating, likedMost, improvements, jobRole

üîß FIELD MAPPING GUIDE

Map your survey fields in the "Normalize Survey Response" node:

Required fields:
‚Ä¢ rating: Numeric rating (1-5 or 1-10)
‚Ä¢ likedMost: What attendees liked
‚Ä¢ improvements: Suggested improvements
‚Ä¢ jobRole: Attendee job title
‚Ä¢ companySize: Company size category

Optional fields:
‚Ä¢ email: Contact email
‚Ä¢ attendeeName: Full name
‚Ä¢ sessionAttended: Specific session
‚Ä¢ wouldRecommend: Yes/No recommendation

Adjust field names to match your form structure!

ü§ñ AI PROMPT CUSTOMIZATION

Customize AI analysis in the Information Extractor nodes:

**Individual Response Analysis:**
‚Ä¢ Sentiment: Positive/Neutral/Negative
‚Ä¢ Key points liked (1-2 bullets)
‚Ä¢ Improvement suggestions (1-2 bullets)
‚Ä¢ Testimonial quote (optional)

**Aggregate Summary:**
‚Ä¢ Overall sentiment trend
‚Ä¢ Top 5 themes from all responses
‚Ä¢ Top 5 action items
‚Ä¢ Average rating context

Modify the schema in both AI nodes to match your analysis needs!

üìä AGGREGATION BRANCH

This branch is triggered when you want to analyze ALL responses:

1. The IF node checks for a manual trigger flag
2. Get All Responses pulls data from Google Sheets
3. Aggregate Ratings collects all rating values
4. Calculate Average computes the mean rating
5. AI Aggregate Summary generates insights
6. Results posted to Slack and appended to Doc

To trigger: Set a flag in Workflow Configuration or use a manual execution button!

## üõ°Ô∏è ERROR HANDLING
Checks AI output exists. . IF no AI output ‚Üí Slack alert + skip

üìÑ GOOGLE DOCS	
Logs full feedback ‚Üí Running event report

üìã SETUP INSTRUCTIONS

1. Choose your trigger:
   ‚Ä¢ Survey Webhook: For Google Forms/Typeform webhooks
   ‚Ä¢ Google Sheets Trigger: For polling a responses sheet

2. Configure Workflow Configuration node:
   ‚Ä¢ eventName: Your event name (e.g., "Tech Summit 2024")
   ‚Ä¢ slackChannel: Channel ID for #event-feedback
   ‚Ä¢ googleDocId: ID of your feedback document
   ‚Ä¢ spreadsheetId: (Optional) Google Sheets ID for aggregation

3. Set up credentials:
   ‚Ä¢ Slack OAuth2 API
   ‚Ä¢ Google Docs OAuth2 API
   ‚Ä¢ Google Sheets OAuth2 API (if using Sheets trigger)
   ‚Ä¢ OpenAI API credentials

4. Test with sample data before going live!

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
